body_html: @jli05: https://docs.python.org/3/whatsnew/3.4.html makes it look like supporting 3.3 won't be any harder than 3.4, so we should be good to go. It is possible our internal tests will be run only in 3.4 (and 2.7), but if anything ever breaks we'll be happy to accept patches.
